THE Tennis Section of the Lagos Country Club, Ikeja will be in the spotlight from April 11-16 as the Prince Ademiluyi Memorial Tennis Tournament holds. According to Ehi Ujiagbe, the captain of the Tennis Section, no fewer than 60 kids are scheduled to feature. He added that kids are excited at the return of the tournament which was forced to be put on hold for the last few years due to Covid-19. Ujiagbe hinted that the six-day program, which is the 16th edition, will begin as a clinic and end up as a tournament and is open to kids from ages 3-to 18.   Tuchel reads riot act to Chelsea stars after dismal week     Arteta admits Partey may not return this season     AFCON 2023: Two qualifiers moved after Tunisia consider a…   He stated that the Ademiluyi Memorial Tournament is one of the legacies of Dr. Ademiluyii, an ardent tennis fan, who was a staunch member of the tennis section. “Being one of the longest-running junior programs in the club we look forward to a memorable tournament. “It’s a matter of fact that Ademiluyi tournament has helped in the development of Nigerian tennis over the decade as some of the top players both on the junior and senior ranks were products of this program.” Tennis equipment, as well as certificates, will be given to kids that excel in the tournament.